The paper discusses the development of a network architecture to enable broadband connectivity in rural areas, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves addressing challenges associated with high-speed connectivity, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The paper also mentions building a testbed, which could be related to computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
